{{Infobox rockunit | name = Caranguejeira Conglomerate | image = | caption = | type = [[Geological formation]] | period = Cenomanian | age = [[Aptian]]-[[Cenomanian]] | prilithology = [[Conglomerate (geology)|Conglomerate]] | otherlithology = | namedfor = | namedby = | region = [[Santarém District|Santarém]] | country = {{POR}} | coordinates = {{coord|39.7|N|8.6|W|display=inline,title}} | paleocoordinates = {{coord|29.6|N|1.9|W|display=inline}} | unitof = | subunits = | underlies = | overlies = | thickness = | extent = | area = | map = | map_caption = }}
The '''Caranguejeira Conglomerate''' ({{lang-pt|Conglomerados de Caranguejeira}}) is an [[Aptian]] to [[Cenomanian]] geologic [[Formation (geology)|formation]] in [[Portugal]]. [[Dinosaur]] remains diagnostic to the [[genus]] level are among the fossils that have been recovered from the formation.<ref name="dinosaurdistribution">Weishampel, et al. (2004). "Dinosaur distribution." Pp. 517-607.</ref>
