'''Kopačka''' ({{lang-mk|Копачка}}) is a [[folklore]] [[musical ensemble]] from [[Dramče]], [[Republic of Macedonia]]. Founded in 1948, it is the oldest of its kind in the Republic of Macedonia, even older than the most famous Macedonian folklore ensemble [[Tanec]], which was founded in 1949. The ensemble is best known for the dance with the same name [[Kopačka (folk dance)|''Kopačka'']].

In November 2008, the Kopačka ensemble marked its 60 years jubilee. There was also a guest ensemble from [[Melnik, Bulgaria]].

