'''Ondangwa Constituency''' was an [[Constituencies of Namibia|electoral constituency]] in the [[Oshana Region]] of [[Namibia]] until August 2013. It had 29,783 inhabitants, its district capital was the town of [[Ondangwa]].<ref>[http://www.statoids.com/yna.html Constituencies of Namibia, 2004]</ref> Following a recommendation of the ''Fourth Delimitation Commission of Namibia'', and in preparation of the [[Namibian general election, 2014|2014 general election]], the constituency was split into [[Ondangwa Urban]] and [[Ondangwa Rural]].<ref name=split>{{cite news |url=http://www.newera.com.na/articles/53580/President-divides-Kavango-into-two |title=President divides Kavango into two |last=Nakale |first=Albertina |date=9 August 2013 |newspaper=[[New Era (Namibia)|New Era]]}}</ref>
