'''Presidential elections''' were held in the [[Republic of the Congo]] for the first time on 26 March 1961. The only candidate was the incumbent, [[Fulbert Youlou]] of the [[Democratic Union for the Defense of African Interests]], who was re-elected unopposed.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/cg.html Elections in Congo-Brazzaville] African Elections Database</ref> Voter turnout was 90.3%.<ref>Nohlen, D, Krennerich, M & Thibaut, B (1999) ''Elections in Africa: A data handbook'', p273 {{ISBN|0-19-829645-2}}</ref>
