{{Infobox settlement <!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions --> | official_name = Southern Albania | native_name = Shqipëria jugore | settlement_type = Region | image_map = | map_caption = | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{ALB}} | area_total_km2 = 12,989 | area_footnotes = | population_as_of = | population_total = 920,448 | population_footnotes = | population_density_km2 = auto | blank_name_sec1 = [[Nomenclature of Territorial Units for Statistics|NUTS]] code | blank_info_sec1 = AL03 | blank_name_sec2 = | blank_info_sec2 = }} [[File:NUTS of Albania (AL).png|140px|right|thumb|Southern Albania is in blue.]] '''Southern Albania''' is one of the three [[Nomenclature of Territorial Units for Statistics|NUTS-2 Regions]] of [[Albania]].<ref>{{cite web|title=NUTS of Albania|url=http://www.instat.gov.al/media/204367/gdp_by_statistical_regions_level_2__3_year__2011.pdf|publisher=INSTAT|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924035535/http://www.instat.gov.al/media/204367/gdp_by_statistical_regions_level_2__3_year__2011.pdf|archivedate=2015-09-24|df=}}</ref> It consists of five counties: [[Berat County|Berat]], [[Fier County|Fier]], [[Gjirokastër County|Gjirokastër]], [[Korçë County|Korçë]] and [[Vlorë County|Vlorë]].
In Greece, a subset of the region, including the Southern-most areas as well as areas near the Greek border, is known as [[Northern Epirus]].<ref>{{cite book|author=Southern Albania|title=Southern Albania, 1912-1923|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=n4ymAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA1|publisher=Stanford University Press|isbn=978-0-8047-6171-0|pages=1–}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Edith Pierpont Stickney|title=Southern Albania Or. Northern Epirus in European International Affairs: 1912-1923|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sHArAAAAIAAJ|year=1926|publisher=Stanford University Press}}</ref>
